Prepare cake batter according to directions on box. Add MILKY WAY(R) Bars to batter before filling paper lined cupcake cups. Bake in a preheated 350 degrees F oven for approximately 21 to 24 minutes. Cool completely. Tint 1/2 cup frosting yellow, set aside. Tint remaining frosting blue and cover the cupcakes. Sprinkle frosting with candy glitter. Press one TWIX(R) Cookie Bars, standing straight up, into the center of each cup. Dot the top of each TWIX(R) Cookie Bars with yellow frosting and attach a yellow M&M'S(R) Brand Chocolate Candies. Arrange nine cupcakes into a line, creating a menorah. Lift the center (fifth in line) cupcake slightly.